>> What is a good desk mike to use on the Flex-3000?
>>
>
> I use the Yamaha CM500 recommended on this list (headset and boom mic,
> about $50) and it works a treat.  Be sure to put a couple of ferrites
> around the audio input to the F3K to kill any RF picked up in the wire.
> You need to make your own adaptor to the RJ45 on the front panel for the
> mic/headset/ptt switch.
>
> There is another headset, highly recommended, using a OVL750MV headset
> with boom mic, that includes all the cable wiring done for you.  It is sold
> by someone on the list, but I can't remember who.
